    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-19T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-19T03:00:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/457: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davies</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-19T11:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 19, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 19—5:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>177. Department’s 102, July 17, 2 p.m. Yesterday was a rest day and no business
                    could be done with the Foreign Office. The tentative addition to the exceptions
                    to the exportation clause, cited in the Department’s telegram under reference,
                    was shown this morning to <persName corresp="#p_NAF1">Neymann</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_RBD1">Rosenblum</persName>. They stated that while
                    they were not in a position to give a final decision on spot they saw no
                    objection to the inclusion of this exception and did not anticipate that there
                    would be any.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davies</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
